I did experience a bit of "warm up" action. It isn't very severe. It
isn't enough drag on a cold morning to prohibit using the slow speed
which need to keep turning to make the connection again.

> We were worried that the white litium would be too thin
> and leak too easily past the shaft seals.  Thusly gunking up the
> motor armature. 

good thought. I haven't seen any leakage so far. hopefully it will
hold up.

